# 🏋️ AI POSTURE — Full Technical Survey Report

**Generated:** 2026-03-09 | **Project Root:** `c:\Users\beino\Desktop\AI POSTURE`

---

## 1. Project Overview

**AI POSTURE** (internally: *AI Workout Tracker*) is an AI-powered mobile workout tracking application featuring real-time pose detection, form analysis, gamification, multi-language support, and a subscription-based monetisation model. The system is composed of two discrete services:

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|---|---|---|
| Backend | FastAPI (Python) | v1.0.0 |
| Frontend | Flutter (Dart) | v2.0.0+2 |
| Database | PostgreSQL | 16-alpine (Docker) |
| Containerisation | Docker Compose | v3.8 |

---

## 2. High-Level Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Flutter Mobile App                    │
│  (Android / iOS / Web / Windows / Linux / macOS)        │
│  Camera → Google ML Kit → Pose Detection                 │
└────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘
                 │ HTTPS (Dio / REST)
                 ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│             FastAPI Backend (Python)                     │
│  /api/v1/{auth, workouts, analytics, track, admin}      │
│  JWT Auth · Pydantic v2 · SQLAlchemy ORM               │
└────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘
                 │ SQLAlchemy + psycopg2
                 ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  PostgreSQL 16 (Docker Container: ai_posture_db)        │
│  Managed via: Alembic migrations + pgAdmin (optional)   │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## 3. Backend — FastAPI Service

### 3.1 Entry Point & Middleware

**File:** `backend/app/main.py`

- **CORS** middleware: configurable via `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env var (defaults: `localhost:3000`, `localhost:8080`, `10.0.2.2:8000`)
- **Request timing** middleware: injects `X-Process-Time` header on every response
- **Startup hook**: auto-creates all SQLAlchemy tables via `Base.metadata.create_all()`
- **Exception handlers**: covers `RequestValidationError`, `SQLAlchemyError`, and generic `Exception`
- **Swagger UI**: `/docs` | **ReDoc**: `/redoc` | **Health**: `/health`

### 3.2 Configuration

**File:** `backend/app/config.py` — uses `pydantic-settings` with `extra="forbid"` (strict config validation)

| Key | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `API_V1_PREFIX` | `/api/v1` | All routes prefixed here |
| `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES` | `10080` | 7 days |
| `ALGORITHM` | `HS256` | JWT signing |
| `MIN_POSE_CONFIDENCE` | `0.5` | AI inference threshold |
| `DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE` | `20` | Max: 100 |
| `CALORIES_PER_REP` | pushup:0.5, squat:0.32, plank:0.25 | Hardcoded caloric constants |

### 3.3 API Layer — Routers & Endpoints

Prefix: `/api/v1`

| Router File | Prefix | Tag | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `auth.py` | `/auth` | Authentication | Register, login, token refresh, profile |
| `sessions.py` | `/workouts` | Workout Sessions | CRUD for workout sessions |
| `analytics.py` | `/analytics` | Analytics & Stats | User-level stats and progress |
| `tracking.py` | `/track` | Event Tracking | App sessions, screen views, feature usage |
| `admin_analytics.py` | `/admin/analytics` | Admin Analytics | Business metrics, revenue, retention |
| `payments.py` | `/payments` | Payments | Stripe & Flutterwave integration |
| `ai.py` | *(unregistered)* | — | AI endpoint stub (empty file) |
| `workouts.py` | *(unregistered)* | — | Workouts endpoint stub (empty file) |

> [!WARNING]
> `ai.py` and `workouts.py` are **empty stubs** not registered in the main router. These represent unfinished or planned features.

### 3.4 Services Layer

| Service | File | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| Auth | `auth_service.py` | Password hashing, JWT creation/validation |
| Session | `session_service.py` | Workout session business logic |
| Workout | `workout_service.py` | Exercise utility logic |
| Email | `email_service.py` | SendGrid email dispatch |
| Pose Analyzer | `ai/pose_analyzer.py` | Pose confidence scoring |
| Calorie Calc | `ai/calorie_calc.py` | Per-rep calorie estimation |
| Stripe | `payments/stripe_service.py` | Stripe subscription management |
| Flutterwave | `payments/flutterwave_service.py` | Flutterwave integration (empty) |
| Payment Endpoints | `payments/payment_endpoints.py` | Webhook handling, checkout sessions |

> [!WARNING]
> `flutterwave_service.py` is an **empty file**. Flutterwave payments are not yet implemented in the backend service layer.

### 3.5 Data Models (SQLAlchemy ORM)

#### `users` table
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | Integer PK | Auto-increment |
| `email` | String (unique) | Auth identity |
| `hashed_password` | String | bcrypt |
| `gender` | Enum | male/female/other |
| `fitness_level` | Enum | beginner/intermediate/advanced |
| `is_premium` | Boolean | Subscription flag |
| `stripe_customer_id` | String | Stripe customer ref |
| `is_admin` / `is_verified` | Boolean | Role & verification |

#### `workout_sessions` table
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `exercise_type` | String | pushup/squat/plank etc. |
| `total_reps` / `correct_reps` | Integer | Raw + validated reps |
| `average_accuracy` | Float | 0.0–100.0 |
| `reps_data` | JSON | Per-rep breakdown array |
| `device_type` | String | ios/android |

#### Analytics Tables (11 total)
- `app_sessions` — App open/close tracking with device, OS, location, network
- `screen_views` — Per-screen navigation events
- `feature_usage` — Named feature interaction events
- `user_demographics` — One-to-one user profile enrichment
- `subscription_events` — Full audit trail of plan changes
- `retention_cohorts` — Week-0 through week-12 retention grid
- `revenue_records` — Daily revenue with MRR contribution
- `error_logs` — Client-side error capture with stack trace

### 3.6 Database Migrations (Alembic)

- Root-level `alembic.ini` + `alembic/` directory for migration management
- Backend-level `backend/alembic/` directory (dual Alembic setup — potential conflict)

> [!CAUTION]
> There are **two Alembic directories**: one at the project root and one inside `backend/`. Ensure migrations are always run from the correct location to avoid schema drift.

