## 5. Infrastructure & DevOps

### 5.1 Docker Compose Services

| Service | Image | Port | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `postgres` | postgres:16-alpine | 5432 | Named volume `postgres_data` |
| `backend` | Custom Dockerfile | 8000 | Hot-reload via `--reload` |
| `pgadmin` | dpage/pgadmin4:latest | 5050 | Optional `--profile tools` |

### 5.2 Networking

- All containers on `ai_posture_network` (bridge driver)
- Backend depends on `postgres` health check before starting

### 5.3 Backend Dockerfile

- Located at `backend/Dockerfile`
- Volume mounts `./backend:/app` for live reload during development

### 5.4 Environment Variables (`.env`)

| Category | Variables |
|---|---|
| Database | `DATABASE_URL`, `DB_PASSWORD` |
| Security | `SECRET_KEY`, `ALGORITHM`, `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES` |
| CORS | `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` |
| Stripe | `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`, `STRIPE_PRICE_ID_MONTHLY/YEARLY` |
| Flutterwave | `FLUTTERWAVE_SECRET_KEY`, `FLUTTERWAVE_PUBLIC_KEY` |
| Email | `SENDGRID_API_KEY`, `FROM_EMAIL` |
| Admin UI | `PGADMIN_EMAIL`, `PGADMIN_PASSWORD` |

> [!CAUTION]
> A `.env` file exists in both the project root (`AI POSTURE/.env`) and inside `backend/.env`. Ensure these are kept in sync to avoid configuration drift between Docker and local development.

